channel.title: Shall i or shall i not?
channel.description:
Well, I'm working on a server (Not to release) but im still learning But i really want to make a development thread, But i haven't added much and i'm still learning and iv'e added a few things but not majors ones.
But i don't want to make a thread wasting my time, Then getting people flaming because i haven't added anything, Shall i or shall i not?
Please help! And iv'e always wanted to make a development thread
And the source/client im using is: Project Insanity

item.title: Shall i or shall i not?
item.dc:creator: @xEthanx xEthanx
item.description:
@xEthanx wrote:

I’d say go for it. Your first server is bound to have a ton of mess ups anyway. Everyone has to start somewhere, why not? I would recommend it just because it’s a good learning experience to go through a few times.

I don’t think you’ll get flamed for posting a development thread as long as you follow the rules of it. The main reason why people get flamed there isn’t because their server sucks, it’s just because they refuse to pay attention to how they’re supposed to post. Anyways, good luck if you do decide to.

Read full topic
item.source: Shall i or shall i not?

item.title: Shall i or shall i not?
item.dc:creator: @Flame3 John
item.description:
@Flame3 wrote:

It’s the little things that count. If you’re comfortable with your progress so far and you think you can provide updates at a steady rate, go for it. Also, if you’re ever facing people being unconstructive and posting things such as “this sucks” or “you won’t get far”, you can just report the post to a moderator.

Read full topic
